message.content:
The start symbol S always expands as

S → NT3 NT77

This means the very first terminal of any sentence in the language must come from the left‐most symbol NT3.

The options for NT3 are
• NT3 → 't17'
• NT3 → NT17 NT6

If NT3 → 't17', the first terminal produced is t17.
If NT3 → NT17 NT6, the first terminal produced comes from NT17.

NT17 can be
• NT17 → 't70'      (first terminal t70)
• NT17 → NT8 NT58   (first terminal comes from NT8)

NT8 can be
• NT8 → 't35'       (first terminal t35)
• NT8 → 't69'       (first terminal t69)
• NT8 → NT30 NT50   (first terminal comes from NT30, which is fixed to the terminal t54)

Therefore the very first terminal that NT3 can ever yield is restricted to the set {t17, t70, t35, t69, t54}.  
The token t29 is not in this set.

Since the given string starts with t29, it cannot be derived from the grammar.

Hence the grammar does not generate the string.

No

The start symbol is  

S → NT3 NT77  

NT3 can either be the single terminal ‘t17’ or the pair NT17 NT6  
( NT6 is the single terminal ‘t63’ ).

There is only one ‘t63’ in the whole string – at position 32.  
Therefore NT6 must correspond to that token, and NT17 has to cover the
first 31 tokens.

NT17 → NT8 NT58  or  NT17 → 't70'  
(‘t70’ occurs only once, at position 21, so the single-token alternative is
impossible: NT17 has to cover all 31 preceding tokens.)

Hence NT17 must use NT8 NT58.

NT8 can yield only  
• the single terminal ‘t35’ or ‘t69’, or  
• the two-token sequence ‘t54 t24’ (NT30 NT50).

Thus NT8 is at most 2 tokens long.  
Consequently NT58 has to cover the remaining 29 or 30 tokens.

But NT58 has only two possibilities:

1. NT58 → 't54'  (one token)  
2. NT58 → NT5 NT85 where NT5 is the single terminal ‘t14’.

So in the second case the very next token after NT8 must be ‘t14’, and
NT85 must generate the rest.

However NT85 can be only

a) NT3 NT67, which obligatorily contributes the terminal ‘t56’, or  
b) NT23 NT16, which obligatorily contributes the terminal ‘t29’ or ‘t18’.

None of the first 31 tokens is ‘t56’, ‘t29’ or ‘t18’, therefore NT85
cannot match any part of that prefix.  
Hence NT58 cannot generate 29 or 30 tokens, which means NT17 cannot
generate the first 31 tokens.

Since NT3 cannot produce the required prefix, the start symbol S cannot
produce the whole string, so the string is not in the language of the
grammar.

No
